.TH wxImageList 3 "wx 2.5.4" "Ericsson AB" "Erlang Module Definition"
.SH NAME
wxImageList \- A \fIwxImageList\fR contains a list of images, which are stored in an unspecified form.

.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Images can have masks for transparent drawing, and can be made from a variety of sources including bitmaps and icons.

.PP
\fIwxImageList\fR is used principally in conjunction with \fIwxTreeCtrl\fR and \fIwxListCtrl\fR classes.

.PP
See:


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fIwxTreeCtrl\fR

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fIwxListCtrl\fR

.RE

.PP
wxWidgets docs: wxImageList

.SH DATA TYPES
.LP
.B
\fBwxImageList() :: wx:wx_object().\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.SH FUNCTIONS
.LP
.B
\fBadd(This, Icon) -> integer()\fR
\fB             when\fR
\fB                 This :: wxImageList(),\fR
\fB                 Icon :: wxIcon:wxIcon() | wxBitmap:wxBitmap().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Adds a new image using an icon.

.PP
Return: The new zero-based image index.

.PP
Remark: The original bitmap or icon is not affected by the \fIadd/3\fR operation, and can be deleted afterwards. If the bitmap is wider than the images in the list, then the bitmap will automatically be split into smaller images, each matching the dimensions of the image list. This does not apply when adding icons.

.PP
Only for:wxmsw,wxosx


.RE
.B
\fBadd(This, Bitmap, Mask) -> integer()\fR
\fB             when\fR
\fB                 This :: wxImageList(),\fR
\fB                 Bitmap :: wxBitmap:wxBitmap(),\fR
\fB                 Mask :: wxBitmap:wxBitmap();\fR
\fB         (This, Bitmap, MaskColour) -> integer()\fR
\fB             when\fR
\fB                 This :: wxImageList(),\fR
\fB                 Bitmap :: wxBitmap:wxBitmap(),\fR
\fB                 MaskColour :: wx:wx_colour().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Adds a new image or images using a bitmap and mask colour.

.PP
Return: The new zero-based image index.

.PP
Remark: The original bitmap or icon is not affected by the \fIadd/3\fR operation, and can be deleted afterwards. If the bitmap is wider than the images in the list, then the bitmap will automatically be split into smaller images, each matching the dimensions of the image list. This does not apply when adding icons.


.RE
