.RE
.B
\fBgetIcon(This, Index) -> wxIcon:wxIcon()\fR
\fB                 when This :: wxImageList(), Index :: integer().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns the icon corresponding to the given index.


.RE
.B
\fBgetImageCount(This) -> integer() when This :: wxImageList().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns the number of images in the list.


.RE
.B
\fBgetSize(This, Index) -> Result\fR
\fB                 when\fR
\fB                     Result ::\fR
\fB                         {Res :: boolean(),\fR
\fB                          Width :: integer(),\fR
\fB                          Height :: integer()},\fR
\fB                     This :: wxImageList(),\fR
\fB                     Index :: integer().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Retrieves the size of the images in the list.

.PP
Currently, the \fIindex\fR parameter is ignored as all images in the list have the same size.

.PP
Return: true if the function succeeded, false if it failed (for example, if the image list was not yet initialized).


